http://www.moa.gov.cn/sjzz/syj/dwyqdt/jczt/201402/t20140208_3753906.htm
http://www.moa.gov.cn/sjzz/syj/dwyqdt/jczt/201402/t20140218_3769870.htm
http://www.moa.gov.cn/sjzz/syj/dwyqdt/jczt/201402/t20140225_3796439.htm
March 2014
http://www.moa.gov.cn/sjzz/syj/dwyqdt/jczt/201403/t20140305_3804952.htm

The reports above include also information, which is complementary to that supplied in OIE reports. Examples:

1. In the province Qinghai, during each of the months of September, October, and November 2013, 65 out of the total of 441 serum samples tested, were positive (14.23 percent).

2. In September 2013, there were 10 positive "pathogen monitorings" in Hebei (out of 1000 samples, namely 1.0 percent). Hebei was the site of H7N9 discovery in wild birds.

The MOA reports do not differentiate between the various source(s) of the samples (environmental, animal-derived in markets, their species, poultry farms -- commercial, backyard). Such information is essential for the further study of the LPAI H7N9 epidemiology in animals in China. - Mods.CRD/AS

Maps of China can be seen at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2358899,334. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
